description.narrative: 75 per cent of all public health facilities are equipped and 90 per cent of community health workers have adequate skills to provide quality essential health package of primary health care services, which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, increased proportions of Somalis, especially mothers and children, have equitable access to and use essential health services in targeted areas

description.narrative: UNICEF provided essential equipment & supplies to all 283 supported health facilities (51 SL / 90 PL / 142 CSR), either via the respective MoHs or directly via implementing partners. 45 designated BEmONC facilities (39% of target) were operational 24/7 and UNICEF provided EPHS services in 35 out of 47 districts (14.5% above target). Some 1,146 Community Health Workers were trained to implement integrated community case management. Nevertheless, 511,719 crisis-affected people (68% of target), including 258,070 children under-5 and 151,181 women were provided with curative first consultations by October 2019. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
